### Description

Currently when passing a data model to the signal forms `form()` function and using the `[field]` directive does not work, when a property of the data model is optional.

Consider the following example:

```ts
import { Component, inject, signal } from '@angular/core';
import { Field, form } from '@angular/forms/signals';

interface Book {
  isbn: string;
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  authors: string[];
  description: string;
  imageUrl: string;
  createdAt: string;
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-book-create-page',
  imports: [Field],
  template: `<form (submit)="submitForm($event)">
    <label for="title">Title</label>
    <input type="text" id="title" [field]="bookForm.title" />
    <label for="subtitle">Subtitle</label>
    <input type="text" id="subtitle" [field]="bookForm.subtitle" />
    <!--  ... -->
  </form>`,
  styleUrl: './book-create-page.scss'
})
export class BookCreatePage {
  // Fixme: Only works with "Required<Book>" instead of "Book" since "subtitle" is optional
  readonly #book = signal<Book>({ // <--- ERROR: Type 'MaybeFieldTree<string | undefined, string>' is not assignable to type '() => FieldState<string, string | number>
    isbn: '',
    title: '',
    subtitle: '',
    authors: [''],
    description: '',
    imageUrl: '',
    createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
  });
  protected readonly bookForm = form(this.#book, formSchema);
}
```

As you can see, the type of the data model has an optional field (`subtitle` in this case). In a real-world application this model is probably shared and we want to use it also for the case when storing and retrieving data.
I want to use the model as it is without the need to wrap it in a TS utility like `Required<T>` which will make the optional fields non-optional. But when trying to use the type `Book` in the example directly, I run into a build time error:

```text
‚úò [ERROR] TS2322: Type 'MaybeFieldTree<string | undefined, string>' is not assignable to type '() => FieldState<string, string | number>'.
  Type 'undefined' is not assignable to type '() => FieldState<string, string | number>'. [plugin angular-compiler]

    src/app/books-admin/book-create-page/book-create-page.html:18:36:
      18 ‚îÇ   <input type="text" id="subtitle" [field]="bookForm.subtitle" />
```


### Proposed solution

I would like to allow to pass a model for the form model with optional fields without the need to create a slightly adjusted type for the data model.

### Alternatives considered

As an alternative the fact that we cannot have optional properties and maybe devs should think about using the uitility type `Required<T>` should be considered to include in the upcoming docs.

